@title FaultDisputeGame
 @notice An implementation of the `IFaultDisputeGame` interface.

@notice The absolute prestate of the instruction trace. This is a constant that is defined
         by the program that is being used to execute the trace.
@notice The max depth of the game.
@notice An onchain VM that performs single instruction steps on a fault proof program trace.
@notice The root claim's position is always at gindex 1.
@notice The starting timestamp of the game
@notice An append-only array of all claims made during the dispute game.
@notice An internal mapping to allow for constant-time lookups of existing claims.

returns.createdAt_: The timestamp that the DisputeGame contract was created at.

gameType().details: The reference impl should be entirely different depending on the type (fault, validity)      i.e. The game type should indicate the security model.

returns.gameType_: The type of proof system being used.

initialize().details: This function may only be called once.

params._challengeIndex: The index of the claim being moved against.
params._claim: The claim at the next logical position in the game.
params._isAttack: Whether or not the move is an attack or defense.

resolve().details: May only be called if the `status` is `IN_PROGRESS`.

returns.status_: The status of the game after resolution.

returns.rootClaim_: The root claim of the DisputeGame.

step(uint256,bool,bytes,bytes).details: This function should point to a fault proof processor in order to execute      a step in the fault proof program on-chain. The interface of the fault proof      processor contract should be generic enough such that we can use different      fault proof VMs (MIPS, RiscV5, etc.)

params._claimIndex: The index of the challenged claim within `claimData`.
params._isAttack: Whether or not the step is an attack or a defense.
params._proof: Proof to access memory leaf nodes in the VM.
params._stateData: The stateData of the step is the preimage of the claim at the given        prestate, which is at `_stateIndex` if the move is an attack and `_claimIndex` if        the move is a defense. If the step is an attack on the first instruction, it is        the absolute prestate of the fault proof VM.

returns._0: Semver contract version as a string.

status.return: The current status of the game.

returns._0: The current status of the game.

CannotDefendRootClaim().notice: Thrown when a defense against the root claim is attempted.

ClaimAlreadyExists().notice: Thrown when a claim is attempting to be made that already exists.

ClockNotExpired().notice: Thrown when the game is attempted to be resolved too early.

ClockTimeExceeded().notice: Thrown when a move is attempted to be made after the clock has timed out.

GameDepthExceeded().notice: Thrown when a move is attempted to be made at or greater than the max depth of the game.

GameNotInProgress().notice: Thrown when an action that requires the game to be `IN_PROGRESS` is invoked when         the game is not in progress.

InvalidParent().notice: Thrown when a step is attempted above the maximum game depth.

InvalidPrestate().notice: Thrown when an invalid prestate is supplied to `step`.

ValidStep().notice: Thrown when a step is made that computes the expected post state correctly.

Move(uint256,bytes32,address).notice: Emitted when a new claim is added to the DAG by `claimant`

Resolved(uint8).notice: Emitted when the game is resolved.

ABSOLUTE_PRESTATE().notice: The absolute prestate of the instruction trace. This is a constant that is defined         by the program that is being used to execute the trace.

MAX_GAME_DEPTH().notice: The max depth of the game.

VM().notice: An onchain VM that performs single instruction steps on a fault proof program trace.

addLocalData(uint256,uint256).notice: Posts the requested local data to the VM's `PreimageOralce`.

bondManager().notice: Returns the address of the `BondManager` used.

claimData(uint256).notice: An append-only array of all claims made during the dispute game.

claimDataLen().notice: Returns the length of the `claimData` array.

createdAt().notice: Returns the timestamp that the DisputeGame contract was created at.

gameData().notice: A compliant implementation of this interface should return the components of the         game UUID's preimage provided in the cwia payload. The preimage of the UUID is         constructed as `keccak256(gameType . rootClaim . extraData)` where `.` denotes         concatenation.

gameStart().notice: The starting timestamp of the game

l1BlockNumber().notice: The l1BlockNumber that Cannon was ran from to generate the root claim.

l1Head().notice: Returns the L1 block hash at the time of the game's creation.

l2BlockNumber().notice: The l2BlockNumber that the `rootClaim` commits to. The trace being bisected within         the game is from `l2BlockNumber - 1` -> `l2BlockNumber`.

move(uint256,bytes32,bool).notice: Internal move function, used by both `attack` and `defend`.

proposals().notice: The starting and disputed output proposal for the game. Includes information about         the output indexes in the `L2OutputOracle` and the output roots at the time of         game creation.

resolve().notice: If all necessary information has been gathered, this function should mark the game         status as either `CHALLENGER_WINS` or `DEFENDER_WINS` and return the status of         the resolved game. It is at this stage that the bonds should be awarded to the         necessary parties.

status().notice: Returns the current status of the game.

step(uint256,bool,bytes,bytes).notice: Perform the final step via an on-chain fault proof processor

version().notice: Returns the full semver contract version.
